## Agent Categories - CRITICAL DISTINCTION

### Implementation Agents (write code - use for ALL implementation tasks)

| Agent | Language/Stack | Use For |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| **bolt** | Kubernetes/Helm | Infrastructure provisioning (Task 1 ONLY) |
| **rex** | Rust/Axum/Tokio | Rust backend services |
| **grizz** | Go/gRPC/Chi | Go backend services |
| **nova** | Bun/Elysia/Effect/Drizzle | TypeScript backend services |
| **blaze** | Next.js/React/shadcn | Web frontends |
| **tap** | Expo/React Native | Mobile apps |
| **spark** | Electron | Desktop apps |

### Support Agents (review only - run AFTER implementation)

| Agent | Role | Use ONLY For |
|-------|------|--------------|
| **cleo** | Quality Review | Code review AFTER implementation PR is created |
| **cipher** | Security Audit | Security audit AFTER implementation PR is created |
| **tess** | Testing | Writing tests AFTER implementation PR is created |
| **atlas** | Integration | Merging PRs AFTER all reviews pass |

**CRITICAL RULE**: `cipher`, `cleo`, `tess`, and `atlas` are NEVER assigned to implementation tasks. If a task involves writing code (auth, API endpoints, UI components, etc.), it MUST use an implementation agent (bolt/rex/grizz/nova/blaze/tap/spark).

