## Quality Checklist (VERIFY EVERY ITEM)

Before finalizing:

- [ ] **Service table created** - All services from PRD identified with tech stacks
- [ ] **Task 1 is `agentHint: "bolt"`** - Infrastructure MUST be first
- [ ] **Every task has `agentHint` set** - No null or empty values
- [ ] **Implementation agents only for code tasks:**
  - [ ] Rust tasks → `rex`
  - [ ] Go/gRPC tasks → `grizz`
  - [ ] Node/Bun/TypeScript API tasks → `nova`
  - [ ] Frontend/Dashboard/UI tasks → `blaze`
  - [ ] Mobile/Expo tasks → `tap`
  - [ ] Desktop/Electron tasks → `spark`
  - [ ] Infrastructure/K8s tasks → `bolt`
- [ ] **Support agents ONLY for review/audit tasks:**
  - [ ] `cipher` ONLY for "Security Audit", "Security Review", "Vulnerability Scan"
  - [ ] `cleo` ONLY for "Code Review", "Quality Review"
  - [ ] `tess` ONLY for "Write Tests", "E2E Testing", "Test Suite"
  - [ ] `atlas` ONLY for "Merge PRs", "Integration"
- [ ] **Code signatures in details** - Every implementation task has language-appropriate signatures
- [ ] **No auth/jwt/oauth tasks assigned to cipher** - These are implementation!
- [ ] **Dependencies form valid DAG** - No cycles
- [ ] **Implementation tasks depend on task-1** - Infrastructure first
- [ ] **Each task is atomic** - Completable in one PR

**VALIDATION**: Count agent assignments. If `cipher` has more than 0-2 tasks (security audits only), you have made a mistake.

